  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">219026 WFP FY22 South Kivu GFD</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is planned to meet immediate food and nutrition needs of 160,161 vulnerable people (38,146 men, women 40,280, 40,500 boys and 41,235 girls) who are new IDPs, new returnees and host communities in the territories of Walungu, Kalehe, Fizi, Uvira, Mwenga, Shabunda and Kabare in South Kivu Province.
 
  Due to the nature of gradual movement of the population, it is envisaged that assistance to the entire 160,161 beneficiaries will take place in batches. Monthly distributions of dry rations (cereal, pulses, oil and salt) will be provided to the targeted beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
